==English==

===Etymology===
{{L.}} ''abortio'', from ''aboriri''; see also [[abort]].

===Noun===
'''abortion''' (''plural'' '''abortions''')

#<!--DefA-->The act of terminating a [[pregnancy]], resulting in the death of an [[embryo]] or a [[fetus]].
#<!--DefB--> The natural or accidental termination of a pregnancy before the [[embryo]] or [[fetus]] is capable of surviving; also called [[miscarriage]].
#<!--DefC--> The [[immature]] product of an [[untimely]] birth.
#<!--DefD--> {{biology}} Arrest of development of any organ, so that it remains an [[imperfect]] formation or is [[absorbed]].
#<!--DefE--> Any fruit or produce that does not come to [[maturity]], or anything which in its progress, before it is [[matured]] or perfect
#<!--DefF--> A complete failure.
#:''His attempt proved an '''abortion'''.''
#<!--DefG-->The act of aborting a project, a mission, etc, before it is completed.

